6.2.20  11:55 pm   Im having no inspiration when im trying to produce tracks. Whenever I try making a track i just feel like nothing fits and sit in my chair for hours and just end up giving up because "nothing works." did you suffer this and are there any tips to get OVER this?

      i don't know yet whether you do your writing before recording or if you actually try to do songwriting in the recording studio. but if you are one of those people that tries to write while recording the track, then based on your description of the problem i would highly recommend getting your writing entirely done before you start creating the track. this does not mean you have to know every instrument and every sound etc, but, what i recommend, is that you know every word, melody, chord, every bar, most importantly that you know the exact road map from beginning to end. Then the recording process becomes a fun adventure for how you are going to deliver the song, and you already know the agenda for every part (every bar, not instrument) of the song. forgive me if you already do this. if you have, then my answer would be different

6.2.20  9:03 pm   How do you get over the hurdle of not quite trusting your own ears and thinking you need a second opinion?

     what usually works is to hear it again for the first time after not hearing it for a while. however, the problem with this is it wastes time. in general, it will probably help to try to complete the project in a relatively swift and quick manner. the doubt tends to get worse as the project goes on

     You've talked a lot about making what you alone like,

     that's not quite right, i believe that you must make what you like, but, doing this will also naturally cause others to like it. making what you like, i believe, is the only way to actually end up with something that anyone else will like. so in that case, doing what ONLY you like is probably impossible actually

      but when it comes to production, I don't trust my ears enough to know what sounds "good." Is there even such a thing as good?

     good is more like a feeling. music can bring these feelings, but there are a lot of factors involved with what actually causes which feelings and when and why

     Is it weak to seek a second opinion because it might ruin the genuine me-ness of the project? 

     no
